  "raw_response": "{\n  \"title\": \"NQ 1-Minute Structure Validation After Buy Side Liquidity Sweep of 15-Minute High\",\n  \"school\": \"ICT\",\n  \"asset\": \"NQ1!\",\n  \"timeframe\": \"1M\",\n  \"market_context\": \"Intraday price action during New York session after sweeping a 15-minute high (buy-side liquidity). Analyst observes structure formation on 1-minute chart, labeling short-term, intermediate-term, and long-term highs/lows as price breaks prior structure.\",\n  \"key_observation\": \"Price swept a 15-minute high (BSL), then formed a short-term high, followed by another short-term high on the right side, validating an intermediate-term high; later swept that to form a long-term low after hitting drawn liquidity at 15-minute lows.\",\n  \"analysis_steps\": [\n    \"Step 1: Identified a sweep of a 15-minute high (buy-side liquidity) and labeled subsequent peaks as short-term highs (STH).\",\n    \"Step 2: Waited for and confirmed a second short-term high on the right side of the first STH to classify it as an intermediate-term high (ITH).\",\n    \"Step 3: Observed price reaching the drawn liquidity at 15-minute lows, then breaking the prior short-term high to signal a potential market structure shift.\",\n    \"Step 4: Labeled the new swing low as a short-term low (STL), then awaited a second STL on the right side to validate an intermediate-term low (ITL).\",\n    \"Step 5: Confirmed the long-term low after two STLs flanking a central low, and noted price moving higher into discount zone with fair value gap as POI.\"\n  ],\n  \"ou",
